4 A BILL
5 TO BE ENTITLED
6 AN ACT
7 To alter, rearrange, and extend the boundary lines and
8 corporate limits of the City of Demopolis in Marengo County.
9 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
10 Section 1. The boundary lines and corporate limits of
11 the City of Demopolis in Marengo County are altered and
12 rearranged to include within the corporate limits of the
13 municipality, in addition to the lands now included, all of
14 the following territory:
15 A parcel located in the East Half of Section 29 in
16 Township 18 North, Range 4 East, Hale County, Alabama and
17 being more particularly described as follows;
18 As a STARTING POINT, begin at the Southwest corner of
19 the Southeast Quarter of Section 29, thence proceed North
20 2,673 feet to a point; thence turn and proceed Northeastwardly
21 371 feet to a point; thence proceed North 1,561 feet to the
22 South right-of-way of U.S. Highway 80; thence turn and proceed
23 Southeastwardly along the South right-of-way of U.S. Highway
24 80 to the East boundary of Hale County Tax Parcel No.
25 36-22-09-29-0-000-002.000 (McCants Tract); thence proceed
26 South along the East boundary of the McCants Tract to the West
27 right-of-way of the new West Alabama Highway Project; thence
28 proceed Southwestardly along the West right-of-way of said
Page 1

proceed Southwestardly along the West right-of-way of said
HB613 Engrossed
29 West Alabama Highway Project to the South boundary of Section
30 29; thence turn and proceed West to the STARTING POINT. Said
31 parcel containing 116.00 acres, more or less, in the East Half
32 of Section 29, Township 18 North, Range 4 East, Hale County,
33 Alabama.
34 Section 2. In accordance with Section 11-42-6 of the
35 Code of Alabama 1975, a map showing the proposed territory to
36 be altered, rearranged, and extended from the City of
37 Demopolis is on file and open to public inspection in the
38 office of the Judge of Probate in Marengo County, Alabama.
39 Section 3. This act shall become effective on October
40 1, 2026.
